parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Intermittent Throttle Pedal Sticking and Sudden Acceleration
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent sticking of the throttle pedal can cause sudden acceleration, which can lead to accidents, loss of control, and injury to occupants or other road users.
symptoms: The throttle pedal sticks when depressed
resulting in a loss of power
followed by a sudden power surge

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the throttle body can cause a loss of power, stalling, or sudden acceleration, which can lead to accidents, loss of control, and injury to occupants or other road users.
symptoms: resulting in a loss of power

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the TCM can cause a loss of power, stalling, or sudden acceleration, which can lead to accidents, loss of control, and injury to occupants or other road users.
symptoms: The vehicle loses power without warning
and may require replacement of the computer chip within the transmission.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front strut can cause the vehicle to lose directional control, leading to accidents or near-miss situations.
symptoms: or pulls to one side while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Premature Wear of Front Lower Control Arms
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The premature wear of the front lower control arms can cause the vehicle to lose directional control, leading to accidents or near-miss situations.
symptoms: The vehicle may exhibit uneven tire wear
pull to one side while driving

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cooling system can cause the heater to stop working, leading to discomfort and potential engine damage.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Parts Availability Issues for Vehicle Recalls
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unavailability of parts for vehicle recall items can delay necessary repairs, putting the vehicle and its occupants at risk.
